    that is subject to change without notice and cannot be referred to or relied upon as a final ISO&#xD;
    standard.&lt;/em>&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br /></mainDescription>
  <sections xmi:id="_2mcsMJd0EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Tailor safety lifecycle if it is required" guid="_2mcsMJd0EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The safety lifecycle can be tailored under certain conditions, these conditions are outlined in ISO 26262, volume 2,&#xD;
    Clause 5.4.5.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is expected that any tailoring of the safety lifecycle&amp;nbsp;shall be based upon the&amp;nbsp;reference safety&#xD;
    lifecycle&amp;nbsp;shown below.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp; &lt;img style=&quot;WIDTH: 477px; HEIGHT: 552px&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; src=&quot;./resources/reference%20pahse%20model.png&quot; width=&quot;600&quot;&#xD;
    height=&quot;600&quot; />&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_D3N-sJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Update and refine project plan" guid="_D3N-sJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>Based upon the tailoring of the safety lifecycle and the other supporting documentation around the functional safety&#xD;
concept and architectural assumptions input to this task the project plan is updated.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_G9GxkJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Update and refine safety plan" guid="_G9GxkJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Based upon the tailoring of the safety lifecycle and the other supporting documentation around the functional safety&#xD;
    concept and architectural assumptions input to this task the&amp;nbsp;safety plan is updated.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The safety plan should also be updated with a&amp;nbsp; task covering &lt;a class=&quot;elementLink&quot;&#xD;
    href=&quot;./../../process.compliance.iso26262.base-ibm/capabilitypatterns/8.9%20Verification%20Planning_831C2385.html&quot;&#xD;
    guid=&quot;_91quQZEZEeCUs8vNyweFYw&quot;>8.9 Verification Planning&lt;/a>&amp;nbsp;using ISO volume 4, clauses 6.4.12 and 7.4.11 as&#xD;
    &amp;nbsp;guidance.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_JhxGsJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw" name="Develop item integration and testing plan" guid="_JhxGsJd1EeCPtY0LnWkRDw">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    The planning of the item integration and test plan is heavily dependent upon the ASIL levels of the item(s) being&#xD;
    developed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    It is recommended that the user refers to ISO 26262, volume 4, clauses 8.4.2 to 8.4.4 which indicates which sort of&#xD;
    tests are applicable for&amp;nbsp;the types of subsystem or item&amp;nbsp;under development given their particular ASIL&#xD;
    rating.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <purpose>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Determine and plan the functional safety activities during the individual subphases of system development.&#xD;
&lt;/p></purpose>
</org.eclipse.epf.uma:TaskDescription>
